	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />The best NES homebrew is currently NESnake2. I'm sorry but I don't know where you can download it, but you should do some search.
<br />Other than that, only really simple games or technical demos were made by people from NESdev.
<br />
<br />Because it's really subjective what is a good hack or a bad hack, it's hard to recommend you some. Just go to <!-- w --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.romhacking.net">www.romhacking.net</a><!-- w --> to find the most common NES hacks.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


